sentences.english: The result: Philly had one of the highest death rates in the country.
sentences.chinese: 結果卻導致費城的死亡率高居全美前列。

sentences.english: He topped the list in this appraisal of science and research.
sentences.chinese: 這次科研評比，他高居榜首。

sentences.english: The percentage of revenue in GDP has been among the highest in the world.
sentences.chinese: 我國的電信收入佔GDP之比例已高居世界前列。

sentences.english: Ancient of Days, who sit test throne in glory.
sentences.chinese: 萬世之宗，高居寶座榮耀中。

sentences.english: Colorado Springs has the second highest number of suicides in the nation.
sentences.chinese: 科羅拉多州斯普林斯地區的自殺率高居全國第二。

sentences.english: China is still leading the Olympics 2008 gold medal tally race with 17 golds.
sentences.chinese: 中國隊目前仍以17塊金牌高居金牌榜榜首。

sentences.english: In fact, Shenzhen also has a huge number of women who owns their business or shops.
sentences.chinese: 該地自己擁有事業的婦女比例亦高居全國之冠。

sentences.english: Finland, which topped the league for many years, has dropped to sixth.
sentences.chinese: 曾高居榜首多年的芬蘭跌至第六位。

sentences.english: The high unemployment rate in the U.S. remains one of the biggest worries for investors.
sentences.chinese: 美國失業率高居不下，依然是投資者最爲擔憂的問題。

sentences.english: The African Region’s neonatal death rate is the highest in the world.
sentences.chinese: 非洲區域的新生兒死亡率在全世界高居榜首。
